snippet.textDisplay:
I request all to heed this.
You have really done a great job Coke Studio Pakistan.
Embroidery, pottery, quilts, dressing, and much more can be seen, and that is the proof of how much work you have taken from poor Sindhi people of Pakistan for the sake of money and personal fame.
You say, "They sleep on land, how we do on quilts." You have worn shoes on Sindhi cot, and danced in high spirits, while our poor labor carry you on their shoulders, in the same way, as they used to carry the colonists on their shoulders, with empty belly.
